    "exam": "jee-advanced",
    "year": 2006,
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "type": "SCQ",
    "marks": 3,
    "question": "<p>$\\int \\frac{x^2-1}{x^3 \\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}} d x$ is equal to</p>",
    "tags": [],
    "options": [
      "<p>$\\frac{\\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}}{x^2}+\\mathrm{C}$</p>\n",
      "<p>$\\frac{\\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}}{x^3}+\\mathrm{C}$</p>\n",
      "<p>$\\frac{\\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}}{x}+\\mathrm{C}$</p>\n",
      "<p>$\\frac{\\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}}{2 x^2}+C$</p>"
    ],
    "correctOptionIndex": 0,
    "solution": "<p>$$ \\int \\frac{x^2-1}{x^3 \\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}} $$</p>\n<p>Taking $x^2$ from the expression under root</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} & =\\int \\frac{x^2-1}{x^5 \\sqrt{2-\\frac{2}{x^2}+\\frac{1}{x^4}}} d x \\\\ & =\\int \\frac{\\frac{\\left(x^2-1\\right)}{x^5}}{\\sqrt{2-\\frac{2}{x^2}+\\frac{1}{x^4}}} d x \\\\ & =\\int \\frac{\\left(\\frac{1}{x^3}-\\frac{1}{x^5}\\right)}{\\sqrt{2-\\frac{2}{x^2}+\\frac{1}{x^4}}} d x \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Substitute $2-\\frac{2}{x^2}+\\frac{1}{x^4}=u$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &\\text { Differentiating both sides, we have }\\\\ &\\begin{array}{r} \\left(0+2 \\cdot \\frac{2}{x^3}-\\frac{4}{x^5}\\right) d x=d u \\\\ \\Rightarrow \\quad 4\\left(\\frac{1}{x^2}-\\frac{1}{x^5}\\right) d x=d u \\end{array} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &\\text { Now, above integral becomes after substitution. }\\\\ &\\begin{aligned} \\int \\frac{d u}{4 \\sqrt{u}} & =\\frac{1}{4}\\left(\\frac{u^{\\frac{-1}{2}+1}}{\\frac{-1}{2}+1}\\right)+\\mathrm{C} \\\\ & =\\frac{1}{2} \\sqrt{u}+\\mathrm{C} \\\\ & =\\frac{1}{2} \\sqrt{2-\\frac{2}{x^2}+\\frac{1}{x^4}}+\\mathrm{C} \\\\ & =\\frac{1}{2} \\frac{\\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}}{x^2}+\\mathrm{C} \\\\ & =\\frac{\\sqrt{2 x^4-2 x^2+1}}{2 x^2}+\\mathrm{C} \\end{aligned} \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
    "__v": 0,
    "title": "IIT-JEE 2006"
  },
